items.sentence: What was in the report Tom didn\'t want me to see?
Tom didn\'t trust Mary as much as she trusted him.
Tom didn\'t want to play tennis with us yesterday.
Tom didn\'t want to say something he might regret.
Tom didn\'t want to spend any more time in Boston.
Tom was sitting alone in the park, reading a book.
Tom was the one who suggested that we leave early.
I wish I knew where we could find others like Tom.
You\'re not old enough to get a driver\'s license.
You\'re planning to help me tomorrow, aren\'t you?
